<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-36-1124 </DOCNO><TEXT>The well-documented loss of forest cover throughout the world has createda multitude of equally well-documented environmental problems, includingsoil erosion, water pollution, species extinctions, and the buildup ofatmospheric carbon dioxide, a greenhouse gas that is contributing toglobal warming. Recent discussions on the causes of deforestation havefocused on inevitable consequences of poverty and population growth,such as clearing for agricultural, shifting cultivation, and fuel-woodgathering. But according to a recent report from the World ResourcesInstitute (WRI) in Washington, DC, another important often unrecognized,cause of deforestation is bad economic policies in the countries thatown forest resources.</TEXT></DOC>